caption: Really wanted to like this place after reading all the good reviews, but I must have gone in on a bad day. Waited several minutes for anyone to even acknowledge I was there. Took several minutes to even place my order, not very friendly or welcoming at all. Cold brew was weak, and not very good. Sadly I will not be back again.
It was really great.  Clean, friendly staff, service was quick and the food was good. Would definitely recommend that you give it a try
Good food, varied options, nice people! Very small place, meant to pick up and go. Great to take and eat in the park!
BEST SWEETS AND FOOD AROUND!!!  amazing family owned restaurant and lovely staff.  Inside is so "cozy" and I could eat everything on the menu haha

Fantastic prices, quick and friendly service, and delicious food. Put that together with the only regularly available restroom on the park and it's a regular staple for me and my family. If we all go more often maybe they'll be open on Sunday!
Good, but could be better.
I like coffee. Yes.
Cool place
Great food! So exciting to find a place that takes pride in their food.
Great selection and super friendly staff. Will be back!! =)

Amazing burger!  Presentation of the food was spot on. Food tastes super fresh and everyone was so friendly. Due to food allergies, I had a bunless burger and they were very accommodating and put my burger on lettuce for me.

My toddler son & I always make it a point to visit The Cozy Cow whenever we are at Big Spring Park. I’m so grateful for a place like this; such a perfect location. We love their chicken salad (their pimiento cheese sandwich leaves a lot to be desired, but that doesn’t limit your options in the slightest). I really enjoy their iced lattes (my go-to drink). They sell Blue Bell ice cream which is always well-stocked, much to my son’s delight - we can’t leave without some mint chocolate chip. Seating is more limited due to Covid restrictions, and the square footage is not much to begin with, but there is seating outside and also plenty of places for a picnic in the park should all of their tables be occupied. Although Covid has made things more difficult for local businesses, I do appreciate Cozy Cow continuing to offer their services; as such, we will continue to be customers.

Very lovely and aesthetic. The food was amazing and they had a surprisingly large variety to choose from. They also had a very large selection of coffees including frappuccinos. Seating was good and the employees were very helpful and kind. Will 100% come back!!
Everything at this shop is good.  If you are in the area stop by and get a cup of coffee.
Everything I have had here has been very good.

A great coffee shop in a truly superb area. In the heart of downtown Huntsville overlooking big spring park, it's tough to find a more "city cafe" type atmosphere anywhere in the metro area. The espresso was good, not great. A bit on the bitter side (grind too fine??). The iced coffee however was fantastic! A great place to pick up a brew to walk through the city or just to sit overlooking the park.

We visited this coffee ice cream shop on a visit to the park nearby! AMAZING! One of the best Chai lattes ever! I didnt get her name but the staff were so calm and patient! They helped me by giving me a large cup for my toddlers scoop that saved us on the car ride home! Id highly recommend! This place!
One of our favorite local sandwich and icecream shops

My friends had the Matt burgers and I had the Leah burger (veggie burger) and they were all amazing! Hands down best veggie burger I've ever had. It was pretty cheap, too :) This was probably the best part about my stay at the Embassy.
Very tasty ice cream, creative cups, very good home made ice cream, cozy, nice view, clean, friendly service, park on the street.
Yummy food at a fair price ☺ I love that they're located within the park.
The best food and customer service! ❤
One of the best chai tea lattes I've ever had.
Great service. coffee drinks and ssndwiches!
Great not just for coffee, but really good sandwiches/salads etc. Desserts are unbelievable!!!
Fantastic food. Very cozy atmosphere. Very friendly staff. Great prices. A real gem.

Pretty good for pretty good price! Got the loaded sandwich, a hot tea, and a cup of the chicken salad for $13~. Lots of hot tea and coffee options as well as food. Right across from the ymca so going by there after working out is a no brainer!
This was my second time to go there. Food was great! Reasonable price. Great location.
Small secluded sammich shop.. cozy
I love this place.
Good food, milkshakes and coffee.  We really enjoy this place.  Enjoyed their hamburgers, Santa Fa Salad and many other items they have.
Good burgers and coffee

Been hearing great reviews on this place so I stopped by on yday. The wait was really long (about 30 mins) but they had a live, blues band to pass the time. Couldn't decide on oxtail plate or ribs plate so I got both and saved one for lunch the next day. The oxtails and rice was divine!
Such a Quant and comfortable place to have coffee and relax.

Unimpreaive menu, unimpressive food. There was a weird smell, service was horrid, and the food was not worth what they charge. The coffee was bland, and the coffee menu is just lacking. Giving it 2 stars because at least the ice cream wasn't melted.

Parking is very hard to find since this cafe is downtown next to big spring park. All the street parking was full so i ended up having to park in the event parking garage for $5. It would be great if they made a partnership with the garage and did validation.  Outside of the parking situation, the food was pretty good. I ordered a chicken salad sandwich on a croissant and the croissant was great. The chicken salad was a little "pickley" for my taste and i think it may have had dill in it but some people love that. The ice cream seemed very nice and they offer a nice selection of house made pastries as well.  Overall it was a nice little cafe the parking situation is just a bit of a headache due to the location.
We have always had great service when we eat at Cozy Cow.  They are very friendly and the food is fresh and tasty.
Next to a park. You can sit outside with your pet. Great place to excerise.

As the name implies, this is a cozy, quaint place that had almost a hipster feel to it. The family and I went for lunch, and we each got sandwiches. I ordered the pimento sliders which were pretty good. The counter also offered a number of baked goods and sweets which looked delicious, but I did not partake.  Overall, a fine place, but nothing that wowed me. If you're looking for a lunch spot, you could certainly do worse.
Small unimpressive menu but good food, nice location, good view, nice small personal space, icecream, clean, and friendly staff.
Absolutely amazing! What a great little place. And the people! Definitely a destination.it is so worth getting out of you trek to visit.
Always happy with what I get here. We order for lunch at the office quite often & they seem to always get it right. Decent selection of sandwiches, too.
Cute place friendly staff
Good place to eat lunch casual food good service good workers Pleasant and helpful
Very quick and friendly service. The burger I had was great also
Espresso was good, and the young one with me had vanilla icecream. Said it was best she's had.
i absolutely love the cow❤️
Great service and excellent ice cream and  milkshakes. Didn't get a chance to sample the food but from what I gathered from others it was great too.
Great food, great coffee. Super busy when I was there, but worth the line.
It was good for an Icecream Shop and Coffee Bar. We enjoyed it and the prices are reasonable.
Delicious ice cream, i recommended the banana split😋

The coffee is blah.  The tacos are like an over cooked puree of meat like tooth paste, and it matches the personality of the "gluten free...huh?" Service.  Match that with the cafeteria like atmosphere where you serve yourself and the barista stands behind the counter joking and entirely indifferent to the customer. Then they expect a tip.  Its mellinial service meets menial quality at a school cafeteria.  The cow is cozy....not the customer.
Love
Busy place, service was great and friendly. Amazing menu, decent prices. Will go back!

Great little sandwich shop in downtown Huntsville! Their lunch selections are delicious; just pair it with their brewed ice tea! I had the tuna melt sandwich which was pretty good along with 3 desserts (Lemon cake, brownie and chocolate chip cookie brownie) I just had to try them all! My favorite of the 3 was certainly the brownie.

I LOVE this place. The food is good and it's very quaint. Whenever we go to an event down town we walk here to eat. Just always get a drink or bottled water because their normal water always tastes bad. I think that's more the city's fault than theirs though.
Great smoothies, fresh sandwiches and a great service team. Had a great lunch in a great atmosphere (surrounded by adorable cow pictures). Could you ask for more? I dont think so.
Delicious ice cream!
The veggie burger was good. Nice little cafe.
Delicious stuffed baked potato salad!

Awesome Coffee... I've Cream... And Food café in the heart of Huntsville. The food and coffee were amazing. Very fair pricing. Small but nice atmosphere with outdoor seating along with an awesome view. Service was five stars! Perfect for anyone including families.
Great lunch options.
Friendly staff, tasty sandwiches. Cute decor. Would definitely come back👍🏻

Nice little cafe in downtown Hunstville. I had the tuna melt sandwich which was pretty good along with 3 desserts (Lemon cake, brownie and chocolate chip cookie brownie) I just had to try them all! My favorite of the 3 was certainly the brownie.
Excellent breakfast sandwiches and drinks. Very pleased with service!
Great location. Nice people.  Good food.
First time going. I ordered a strawberry banana smoothie, it was very good
Good, clean, good food.
Great ice cream sundae and latte. The owner is very pleasant to talk with. Great location on the park.

Big BLT with cheese was delicious and so was my smoothie. Only complaint is how difficult it was to get inside with a stroller, the table at the very top of the stairs made it really awkward as I couldn't fit around it with the people sitting there.

Milkshakes here are really good! Only complaint is their business hours -- how do you stay in business when you close at 3pm? I've wanted to try the ice cream here for over a year and only today did I make it over on my lunch break.
Small, but cozy like the name. Food is absolutely great!
Worth the trip.. Loved the ice cream with coffee shot
I can't believe I'd never been here before!! I LOVE this place!!  Great people and a seriously yummy sandwich totally made my day :D
Had been a while since I ate at Cozy Cow. Same great food. Turkey sand and ham sandwich both on cranberry walnut bread. So yummy.
Great coffee
Yummy sandwiches. Not much seating. Great ice cream and desserts!

It is hard to find a good place for lunch in a downtown area. The Cozy Cow is a great place. It is a small café with great sandwiches and desserts. They were very busy when I visited but our orders were perfect and the food was excellent.
This was a very cute little place by Big Springs park in downtown Huntsville AL.
Incredibly welcoming and quite reasonably priced!
Great food!
Always good food!
Always great service and Delicious food!
i have no idea what this place is  aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa
Best lunch ever with views of the park - what could be better!
Great breakfast sandwiches and reasonably priced coffee.
My favorite downtown stop.
Had been a while since I ate at Cozy Cow. Same great food. Turkey sand and ham sandwich both on cranberry walnut bread. So yummy.
Great place, kind people

I don't usually bother with writing reviews, but The Cozy Cow needs one. I came in for the first time with a group of 7 people and we all got meals, desserts, and coffee. This is a cute little coffee shop that's not really geared towards large parties, but the time I spent waiting for the all of the food and drinks was still less than I have spent at many drive-thru windows. The staff was very friendly and patient with our large order, read it back to us twice for accuracy, and delivered everything to us exactly as ordered. All of that is enough to warrant becoming a repeat customer, but then there was the food... Everything was delicious, and the desserts were AMAZING. We all sampled each others' meals, and we all agreed that there was nothing we wouldn't order again. From start to finish, it was an awesome meal and an awesome experience. Parking is a bit of a challenge, but if you are going to be going to Big Spring Park, I absolutely encourage you to stop in and give  them a try. I will be returning often!
Decent food for a decent price. Quaint and cozy. The coffee is trash though so don't bother with that. Also, the pimiento cheese is...weird so maybe opt for a different side.
Cozy atmosphere. Food is good and lots of great deserts!
Always yummy food. Great coffee and tea selection.
Beautiful little coffee hideaway with awesome food.
Great little place! Have enjoyed each soup I've tried and their jalapeno bread is wonderful!
Delicious food. Great prices.
My daughter worked here. She was happy with the place and the customers. Good location.
Helpful and friendly.  Wonderful assortment of choices.
This place is awesome!
Came to this restaurant for the first time and was very impressed.  The service was fast, the food was delicious, and the environment was relaxing.  I will absolutely be back!
Best place in Huntsville for a drink or bite to eat in a relaxed environment. As the name suggests, very cozy.
I loved it loved it
Super cute place and yummy food!
A great place to cool off at Big Spring Park. Good food and ice cream, and a nice staff.
Friendly staff and solid selection.
The place was very cute and cozy, selling blue Bell ice cream, coffee, and pastries.
Great for coffee and a bite to eat

We came on St. Patrick's Day, hoping to get a warm bite to eat before the parade. Our first, second, and third chooses had failed us, so we were both desperate and thrilled to happen upon this place in our wanderings.  The fact that we were in the middle of Lent meant I had some self imposed dietary restrictions, but I was still able to find a nice, healthy and tasty option on their menu.  The workers were super friendly and helpful, and they even made some tasty recommendations. I loved that the bagels tasted fresh and that our meals were made to order. If I were in the area more often, I'd be happy to go back more frequently.
This place is so cute! And they don’t just have coffee. They also offer delicious food options!!
Coffee was good, sandwich prices are a little high for what you get. The food is fine but nothing special, I wouldn't send anyone here for the food but I'd eat if I we're here and hungry.
Sandwiches were Delicious, coffee Surperb, and staff very Friendly!😀  Highly recommend after a walk around Big Spring Park. Will be going back!
Delicious coffee
Nice, friendly staff, good coffee and treats. Great location.

One of my favorites little spots for a good sandwich. I usually get the smoked turkey with provolone on cranberry walnut Fred Bread. It's piled thick with turkey.  The grilled pimento cheese is also a winner. I always get a combo and get hand dipped ice cream for my side! They give you a huge serving of ice cream. I've been coming here for over two years and they are consistently good.
Very nice.  Great burger

It's a nice place. I don't drink coffee, so I can't rate the obvious draw of this place.  The smoothies are really good. They have a good selection and every one I've tried, I've been pleased with.  The food is also surprisingly good for a coffee shop. Not a great selection for vegetarians, but I doubt that affects them much at all.
Great sandwiches.

First the times They are opened is 9-5pm but don't serve food until 11-3pm.  This is important if your like me and don't use Facebook, and go there often. They don't have a website, and their times on Facebook (Mobile version) does not reflect the times of lunch. This is why I have given them a low star.  That's said, this is the ONLY complaint I have besides the prices are a tad high. But the food is absolutely delicious and I am unable to give them lower stars because of it. Also their atmosphere is very family friendly and I'd recommend it to anyone.  <Edit> They are really good about making sure they cook it right.  :) +1 star for great service.  <Edit 1 year later> Store is still open. Has a beautiful park outside it's door now. However Steve and the rest of the top notch guys are gone, and the current ones are kinda wishy washy of when their lunch time ends. :/ Kinda disappointed, probably won't go back, but hope for nostalgic reasons it remains in tact.

Good food and friendly staff. They accommodated us with a Groupon mix up. Only con is that the staff needs to be more experienced with Groupon if they're gonna use the service and explain that you can only redeem once so you better use the total value. You can't carry a balance.
One of my favorite lunch spots.  The food is good, and as the name implies, the place is definitely "cozy".  Coffee is excellent as well.
Really good coffee and they have coconut milk for lattes.
Friendly helpful staff. Yummy food, good selection! Clean dining area!
The place is cute but the burgers were premade for quick service. Not a fan of the preformed premade food
Have the best sandwiches, great coffee and teas, owners and the employees are wonderful. My favorite place
Cute and cozy with friendly and patient service! The food was really good too!
Their smoothies are incredible, cant wait to try other menu items.

First time eating at Cozy Cow and was NOT disappointed!   Delicious food and the staff was extremely friendly and helpful .  The cranberry  chicken salad on toasted cranberry bread is probably the best I've ever had.  Can't say enough nice things about the food and service !  Will definitely eat there again.
Good food and atmosphere, friendly service, and affordable prices. Best chocolate malt I've had in a while too!
Burger was pretty good.  They ran out of chicken salad.  Good for them, right?
Nice and cozy with great food.
Great sandwich ice cream and service!
Nice location downtown next to Big Spring Park.  The coffee is very good.  They have a good selection of ice cream too, although I haven't tried it
Great place. Good food, good coffee, and good atmosphere.
Great food especially sandwiches
Good burger.

Aweful this place won't stay in business long. The coffee was aweful burnt & tasted like it was made yesterday. The "wife" owner stated she was giving whole dollars back bc she was too busy to make change. Maybe she needs business 101 again. My friend ordered an iced coffee with creamer. There was more creamer than coffee. If you are a coffee shop your coffee should be amazing. Not your sugar filled mochas'. Just coffee.  A good cup if coffee doesn't need sugar or creamer.
Love the owners and staff. Been a customer since they first opened and I've never had a bad experience. I eat here on average, once a week. Great food and coffee.

Great food for a great price! They also let you turn any of the sandwiches into a panini so I would definitely recommend doing that! And ordering a side of the potato salad! Service is always great too!!
Great food and great location. Amazing fruit smoothies.
Service is amazing. We love to stop in here for a coffee and sandwich on the weekend. Highly recommend!!

Perfect location - great for mid-week breakfast and quick sandwich.  Great burgers.  Right beside the park, so take the kids for ice cream after you feed the ducks.  They'll make you decorative coffee :)
Good hometown feel with great food
Definitely cozy! Obviously family-owned and family-friendly. Good food, good music, and sweet treats!

The tortilla soup was very good.   My wife’s pimento cheese sliders were also good.  It was very clean and unlike many places these days not overly noisy.  Unbeknownst to me, my car keys fell from my jacket pocket as I left.  I did not realize I had left my keys until about 1/2 hour after closing.  I called and spoke to the owner.  He was willing to take time out of his day to meet me to return my keys.  The willingness to go the extra mile for a first time customer and the good food ensures that I will return.
Chicken Wrap and the pickle they provide with it ....so good...
Yummy

The young ladies behind the counter were so helpful and polite. One suggested the peach paradise smoothie and I was so pleased. I removed my boots and took a nap on the floor...that's how cozy I felt. Don't judge me.
Very nice staff, good hot chocolate. Right next to Big Spring Park.
Good place for sandwiches, salad, coffee....right next to the park.
Great smoothies

The staff is always welcoming. The place has a small town coffee shop feel to it. The sandwiches are great. The location is conveniently located next to Big Spring Park. The prices are fair considering how tasty the food is.

They are trying to do and be several things here, but it doesn't work. "Hmmm, their name is "cow", so does that mean ice cream? But wait, there is coffee listed on the wall... oh, and there are food options? But where are the menus? Do i sit to order?..." The result is a lack of focus,  or a clear theme. One good thing is its location: convenient to utilize when visiting the park or when meandering in town.

Friendly service. It was my first time visiting, so I asked for a recommendation and was presented with the pimento cheese sandwich, potato salad, and a pickle.  The pimento cheese was quite good; nice and peppery! The potato salad is the second best I've had in the area. I'll go back.
Fast. Clean. Amazing sandwich and I'm not a sandwich person. Probably the best potato salad I've ever had.

The best! I come down here to pay my power company bill monthly in person and it just across the street. That's so I can have an excuse to come over here and eat least once a month if not more depending on my budget. PS the website is available if you haven't noticed. It now has different hours so check the website or when walking around Big Spring Park. Also check out on Groupon sometimes they have specials there.
Great icecream, however closing at 5pm can be a pain
Very cool little restaurant. Little snacks and appetizers. Good ice cream and dairy delights.
So Quaint!!! Love the food and staff!
Frendly staff, nice little cafe/restaurant. They also serve great ice cream and other desserts.
I eat there a day or two a week and love it!  The hamburgers are delicious and the coffee is great. I also get sandwiches on Fred Bread. Really nice employees and good service. Highly recommend.
The people there are genuinely nice. The coffee and atmosphere great as well. I can't wait to go back.
Quaint restaurant and coffee bar, hamburgers are hand made at time of order. Great coffee, will be back.

I love this place... coffee, free wi fi... what more could a mom want while waiting on her kids to get out of school.  The kids can walk over from the school and get ice cream.  Nice staff and cute indoor area- outdoor seating area is nice when its warm.
